<br>
1) so that it is not obvious that there are 25 people from the same guild in the zone.   You can do a /who all &lt;guild&gt; and still see that there are 25 of them in the zone you're in.  <br>
2) so that alts with lower levels are not seen in the guild.  When they are grouped people will know their level)<br>
3) So that an innitiate does not ruin a guild name if they turn out to be a jerk.  <br>
I thought that one was particularly self explanitory.  <br>
<br>
In all three of those cases you do not want the guild tag showing up.  The idea in 1 and 3 are not to hide your info... but to specifically hide the guild tag.  /role would not do what I stated.  <br>
<br>
Rules 2 and 3 apply to your second question of why anon while xping.   <p><img src=http://www.sherilyn.net/sigs/lybmauv.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukalynntaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalynn Taranis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://server35.hypermart.net/rcschoner/Kitty.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Advocate<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#006400>(1/28/02 12:48:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why do players hide their guild tags? </span><hr size=1> Well not to sound obnoxious or anything, but I bet you that there are some people that don't know that the /role command exists.<br>
